      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, i was looking at some satellite maps of dc and the way the roads and monuments are laid out... it's weird. if you trace the main axes from everywhere, it doesn't just look like urban planning. it looks like it was designed to follow a specific geometric pattern, almost like a sigil or a ritual circuit. do you see what i mean when you look at the layout of the streets and the positioning of the monuments? it feels intentional.",
